cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.Distributed, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the performance and scalability of a blockchain system, which involves distributed computing. 
2. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper proposes a novel approach to transaction execution in a blockchain system, which involves managing a database of transactions. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the security concerns of blockchain systems and proposes a solution to minimize invalid transactions. 
4. cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing) - The paper discusses the distributed nature of blockchain systems and proposes a solution to maximize concurrent execution. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a software solution to improve the performance and scalability of a blockchain system.
